    Process an incoming raw event feed using multiple parser configurations

    Similar to ParserDoFn, but can be used to process an incoming raw event feed that is keyed using an identifier. An arbitrary number of parser configurations and filters can be installed in the class associated with an identifier.

    When the DoFn processes an incoming raw string, it will utilize the configuration and filters associated with the identifier corresponding to the key of the input string.

    The output will be the parsed event, keyed with the same identifier as the raw string.
